              <li>Average lifespan: 6-10 years</li>
              <li>Age more rapidly after maturity</li>
              <li>+7 years per year after age 2</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Why Size Affects Aging</h2>

        <p>The relationship between size and aging in dogs is still being studied, but several factors contribute to this phenomenon:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Metabolic rate:</strong> Larger dogs have higher metabolic rates, leading to faster cellular aging</li>
          <li><strong>Growth hormones:</strong> Rapid growth in large breeds may contribute to earlier aging</li>
          <li><strong>Genetic factors:</strong> Different breeds have evolved with varying lifespans</li>
          <li><strong>Health complications:</strong> Larger dogs are more prone to certain age-related conditions</li>
        </ul>

